BFS avec file¶

In [2]:
Copied! 
from collections import deque

def bfs(G, s):
    visited = [False]*len(G)
    file = deque([s])
    while len(file) > 0:
        u = file.pop()
        if not visited[u]:
            print(u, end=" ")
            visited[u] = True
            for v in G[u]:
                file.appendleft(v)

bfs(G, 0)

BFS avec 2 couches¶

In [3]:
Copied! 
def bfs(G, s):
    visited = [False]*len(G)
    cur, next = [s], []
    while len(cur) + len(next) > 0: # on s'arrête quand les 2 sont vides
        if len(cur) == 0:
            cur, next = next, []
        u = cur.pop()
        if not visited[u]:
            visited[u] = True
            print(u, end=" ")
            for v in G[u]:
                next.append(v)

bfs(G, 0)

Application : calcul de distance¶

In [4]:
Copied! 
def distances(G, s):
    dist = [-1]*len(G)
    file = deque([(s, 0)])
    while len(file) > 0:
        u, d = file.pop()
        if dist[u] == -1:
            dist[u] = d
            for v in G[u]:
                file.appendleft((v, d + 1))
    return dist

distances(G, 0)

Application : calcul de plus court chemin¶

In [5]:
Copied! 
def bfs(G, s):
    pred = [-1]*len(G)
    file = deque([(s, s)])
    while len(file) > 0:
        u, p = file.pop()
        if pred[u] == -1:
            pred[u] = p
            for v in G[u]:
                file.appendleft((v, u))
    return pred

def path(pred, s, v):
    L = []
    while v != s:
        L.append(v)
        v = pred[v]
    L.append(s)
    return L[::-1] # inverse le chemin

pred = bfs(G, 0)
path(pred, 0, 7)
def bfs(G, s): pred = [-1]*len(G) file = deque([(s, s)]) while len(file) > 0: u, p = file.pop() if pred[u] == -1: pred[u] = p for v in G[u]: file.appendleft((v, u)) return pred def path(pred, s, v): L = [] while v != s: L.append(v) v = pred[v] L.append(s) return L[::-1] # inverse le chemin pred = bfs(G, 0) path(pred, 0, 7)
